#MEM id=atlas source=/root/yvon/agent-department/Marketing/atlas/COMMANDS.md
M|atlas|> No terminal commands. Atlas works through prompts, specs, and handoffs.
M|atlas|1. Receive cg brief from Alex (confirm: vtr, goal, platform, timeline)
M|atlas|2. Load `CREATIVE-PRINCIPLES.md` + brand file
M|atlas|3. Write Visual Brief (one paragraph)
M|atlas|4. Produce Mood Board (3 references + direction)
M|atlas|5. Write Style Spec (6-component structured format from CREATIVE-PRINCIPLES.md)
M|atlas|6. Write Prompt Architecture (final prompts, platform-specific)
M|atlas|7. Define Quality Bar (3 binary pass/fail criteria for Pixel)
M|atlas|8. Run AI Slop Test on prompts — rewrite if 2+ fail
M|atlas|9. Hand off complete package to Pixel: Visual Brief + Prompts + Quality Bar
M|atlas|10. Log cg to mem.md
M|atlas|When Stark asks for one image without a full cg:
M|atlas|1. Confirm vtr + platform
M|atlas|2. Write prompt using 6-component framework
M|atlas|3. Run AI Slop Test (mental check)
M|atlas|4. Deliver prompt ready to paste into generation tool
M|atlas|5. No full mood board needed for single requests
